# Guest

## Summary
Guest models one invitee on the wedding guest list. It extends Person, so it inherits `fullName`, `photo`, and the computed `photoURL`, and adds a `category` enum (Bride's Family, Groom's Family, Close Friend, Friends, College, Colleagues, Others), a `vip` boolean, and a `parentGuest` link that is set on a +1 to point back at the guest who brings them. In the Table Seating Planner package, Guest instances are the people you drag onto tables: the planner links to them via `guests = linksToMany(Guest)`, and each Table field tracks its own `seatedGuests`.

## Import
```js
import { Guest } from '../guest';
```

## Usage
Guest is a card, so consuming cards link to it rather than containing it — the same wiring the planner uses:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksToMany } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { Guest } from '../guest';

export class SeatingChart extends CardDef {
  @field guests = linksToMany(() => Guest);
}
```

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.guests @format='embedded' />
```
Renders each linked guest as an avatar row with name, category dot, VIP badge, and +1 attribution.
